# Student Record Management System

A console-based student management system built in C.

## Features
- Login system with SHA-256 hashed password storage
- Add student records (rejects duplicate roll numbers)
- Display all records
- Search student by roll number
- Edit and delete student records
- Change password (hashed with SHA-256)
- Menu loop — program stays open until you choose Exit
- Marks validated between 0 and 100
- NULL checks on all file operations (no crash on missing files)

## What's New in v2
- Fixed double fclose() crash in searchstudent() delete flow
- Fixed segfault when StudentData.txt is missing
- Password is now stored as a SHA-256 hash instead of plaintext
- Added menu loop (v1 exited after a single action)
- Added duplicate roll number check
- Added marks range validation

## How to Compile and Run

### Linux
Install OpenSSL dev headers if you don't already have them:

sudo apt install libssl-dev

Compile:

gcc SRM_v2.c -o SRM_v2 -lssl -lcrypto

Run:

./SRM_v2

### Windows (MSYS2 / MinGW)
Plain MinGW does not ship OpenSSL, so install MSYS2 first: https://www.msys2.org
Then, from the "MSYS2 MINGW64" terminal (not the plain MSYS2 terminal):

pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-gcc mingw-w64-x86_64-openssl

Compile:

gcc SRM_v2.c -o SRM_v2.exe -lssl -lcrypto

Run:

./SRM_v2.exe

## Default Login
User ID: admin
Password: admin123
(created automatically as a SHA-256 hash on first run if password.dat does not exist)

## Troubleshooting

### Linux
Problem: undefined reference to SHA256
Fix: -lssl -lcrypto is missing from the gcc command. It must come after the source file.

Problem: openssl/sha.h: No such file or directory
Fix: sudo apt install libssl-dev

Problem: Login fails no matter what after upgrading from v1
Fix: v1 stored the password as plaintext, v2 stores a hash. Delete the old file first: rm password.dat

### Windows
Problem: openssl/sha.h: No such file or directory
Fix: You're compiling with plain MinGW, which doesn't include OpenSSL. Install it through MSYS2 (pacman -S mingw-w64-x86_64-openssl) and compile from the MINGW64 shell.

Problem: cannot find -lssl or -lcrypto
Fix: You're in the wrong MSYS2 shell. Use "MSYS2 MINGW64", not "MSYS2 MSYS" — the linker paths differ.

Problem: The console window flashes and closes immediately
Fix: Don't double-click SRM_v2.exe. Run it from Command Prompt or PowerShell so the window stays open and you can read the output.

Problem: Login fails no matter what after upgrading from v1
Fix: Same as Linux — delete the old plaintext password.dat before running v2.

### Both platforms
Problem: Records look corrupted or go missing after adding a student
Fix: Close StudentData.txt if it's open in Notepad or another editor. Windows can lock the file while it's open elsewhere.

Problem: Compiled fine but crashes immediately on first run
Fix: Make sure the program has write access to its own folder — it needs to create StudentData.txt and password.dat there.

